      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "9528f6d3_a3164dd7",
      "file_path": "adapter/acumos/tests/test_docker.py",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 48,
      "message": "Hmmm, I had missed your comment before saying that \"Regarding the pyyaml module, the requirements.txt file is a dictionary that is extracted from the model's metadata.json file....\"\n\nDoes that mean that you do NOT need a static copy in the gerrit repo? Is the static file ignored when creating the test container?\n\nIf the static file is NOT ignored, then I'm not sure I understand why it cannot have both of acumos_dcae_model_runner and pyyaml listed in it?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 105,
        "name": "Tony Hansen",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "tony@att.com",
        "username": "TonyLHansen"
      },
      "updated": "2021-12-09 23:53:36.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "58ff6157_95fc2bd8",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "c0586041_e911bcd1",
      "file_path": "adapter/acumos/tests/test_docker.py",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 48,
      "message": "Yes, you are right. The requirements.txt file is not a static file and is created within the docker container of the Acumos adapter based on the metadata of the ML model. It is also deleted once the docker_gen method completes successfully. Hence, we never required this file in the gerrit repo. Also because it is ignored in the test scripts. I will remove it from the repo. I added it thinking that it is needed for reference.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6744,
        "name": "Shabnam Sultana",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "shabnam.sultana@highstreet-technologies.com",
        "username": "Shabnam"
      },
      "updated": "2021-12-10 07:53:15.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9528f6d3_a3164dd7",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "3b2f56c0_d1f3cddb",
      "file_path": "adapter/acumos/tests/test_spec.py",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 35,
      "message": "Dint see update on this comment; shouldn't this be example-model:latest?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 93,
        "name": "Vijay Venkatesh Kumar",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "vijayv81@gmail.com",
        "username": "vv770d"
